column3: str

<UIForeground>F201FC</UIForeground><UIGlow>F201FD</UIGlow> Quest Sync<UIGlow>01</UIGlow><UIForeground>01</UIForeground>
The worried woman has a fuzzy wuzzy problem.
Search for signs of the runaway cat.
Chase down and catch the runaway cat.
Return the runaway cat to the worried woman.
Ah, you there! Have you seen a black cat nearby? She's wearing a red collar with a big bell attached.
We got separated during the upheaval the other day, but I spotted her in the area not too long ago! I tried to tell her there was nothing to be afraid of now, but she didn't seem convinced...
What will you say?
I'm afraid I haven't seen her...
Sounds like you could use a hand.
Meow!
You haven't? In that case, if it isn't too much to ask, perhaps you'd be so kind as to help me look for her?
Are you sure!? Oh, that would be wonderful!
Did you hear that!? Is that you, my precious little fuzzy wuzzy!?
Oh... Don't toy with me like that! To make up for that cruel joke, I think you should help search for her.
If I leave it any longer, I fear she'll get a taste for freedom and never come back! I'm sure you'll be able to coax her back, though. Please, your assistance would mean the world to me!
I sensed something in you the moment we met─I'm all but certain my little fuzzy wuzzy will take a liking to you! So, what do you say? Can I count on you?

Before you set off, there's something you should know: my little fuzzy wuzzy simply adores being chased. When you find her, be sure to play along and tire her out─she'll settle down soon enough. Anyway, I suggest you head to the plaza and take a look around!
As I said, she loves being chased. You'll need to tire her out before trying to catch her! Good luck!
A black cat sporting a fetching red collar eyes you warily. This must be the missing cat you've been asked to track down.
She seems to have identified you as a worthy playmate. You might be able to catch her if you tire her out.
Although you get the impression the cat has near-limitless energy reserves, you resolve to give chase.
Tire the cat out and then get close enough to swoop in and make your catch!
You can stop giving chase by leaving the area. You may try again by surveying the designated location.
Mmmeowww!
How did you fare? Did you find her!?
My little fuzzy wuzzy! Back at last!
You must have given her quite the chase. She looks about ready for a catnap! Honestly, it's a relief to see her unharmed and healthy.

I'm from Tural originally, but I was stranded here after the barrier went up. It was this little scamp's grandma that helped me through those dark days after I realized I'd be unable to return home...
Indeed, I don't know where I'd be without all of my precious little fuzzy wuzzies. Thank you so much for your help!
